Area Code Review Checklist
==============================

Structure
---------
__ Files are divided into directories by type (rooms, monsters etc).
__ Area directory does not contain unused files.
__ Area is portable by changing a header.
__ Variables are as localized as possible.

Naming
------
__ File names are meaningful to a casual viewer.
__ Variables use Hungarian notation.
__ Variables have useful mnemonics.
__ Function names have useful mnemonics.
__ Aliases intended for internal use (not used by players) must
   begin with double underscores, and the coder name. (e.g. __bob_key).
   These aliases are unique to the application.

Code Format
-----------
__ Indentation should is clear and consistent.
__ Code is not crowded (adequate spacing, blank lines etc.)
__ Code is not sparse (not too many blank lines)
__ Code is blocked where possible to collect similar instructions.
__ Difficult/complex/obscure code is commented.
__ Lines of code should 80 characters wide or less where possible.

Object Creation Standard
------------------------
__ All objects use current standards for settings.
__ Deprecated calls are not used.
__ replace_program() is NOT used. (new standard)

Code Correctness and Efficiency
-------------------------------
__ All objects load.
__ Sanity checks and fail outs are appropriately placed.
__ All active code serves a purpose.
__ Code is efficient as possible, without being unreadable.
__ is_clone() checks are used wherever possible.
__ Code performs the tasks intended by designer.
__ All function redefinitions use all formal parameters.
__ All non-void functions return a value.
__ Under no circumstances will a sensitive mind error occur.

